               </msIdentifier>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>List of groups (pittakia) of lessees of state land who made their tax payments in kind; amounts of land, dates and payments of taxes in wheat are given; at the end of each group there is a summation of the total amounts of land held by the group</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers; on the front P.Col. V 1 recto 4</note>
                     <note type="general">There is a large number of vacant spaces left for entries that were never written</note>
                     <note type="general">178 lines of writing in 10 cols. in a fast, small, and irregular hand; the document is incomplete</note>
                     <note type="general">Each pittakion includes 3 to 8 landholders; the first man in each group is the leader (pittakiarches)</note>
                     <note type="general">The members of a pittakion could associate with themselves one or two joint farmers in the lease</note>
                     <note type="general">In the document several estates appear: usiac land is kept apart from other categories of land</note>
                     <note type="general">Members of the pittakion held their land as subtenants of the pittakiarch, but paid their rent in kind to the state; pittakiarchs were responsible in case of default by individuals</note>
                     <note type="general">The leases of land may not have been undertaken on an entirely voluntary basis</note>
                     <note type="general">The document was frequently revised with transfers and additions of holdings</note>
                     <note type="general">If taxes on land distant from Philadelphia were paid in distant granaries, a differential charge was imposed upon taxpayers</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
